    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">Which food pairings bring out the best in premium Chardonnay?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Rich, oaked Chardonnays excel with lobster, roasted chicken, or cream-based sauces that complement their buttery texture and vanilla notes. Crisp, mineral-driven versions from Chablis or cool climates pair beautifully with oysters, sushi, or goat cheese, where the wine's acidity enhances rather than competes with delicate flavors. The key is matching the wine's weight and intensity to the dish—lighter preparations for elegant, mineral styles, and richer dishes for more opulent expressions.</p>
